<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="537" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d537fn1">Presumably
                                sent via military channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-03">3 January 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>To the President from <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName>.</p>
                        <p>After reading the Prime Minister’s number 530 to you, I wanted you to
                            know that a message from Mister <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName> instructed me to take up the question of what was
                            said in relation to unconditional surrender at Teheran with the Prime
                            Minister on his return to London<note n="2" xml:id="d537fn2">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_855">p.
                                855</ref>.</note>… I hope the Prime Minister’s query to you was in a
                            form acceptable to you. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> meant
                            it to be so and the Prime Minister followed his suggestion in his cable
                            to you. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> thought that the
                            subject had come up at a luncheon conversation at the Russian Embassy.
                            There has been no further word from <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>